article.description: — Nick Jourdain had a career-high 24 points as Temple edged past Tulsa 69-64 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Jourdain scores 24 to lift Temple past Tulsa 69-64
article.linkText: Jourdain scores 24 to lift Temple past Tulsa 69-64
article.story: TULSA, Okla. -- — Nick Jourdain had a career-high 24 points as Temple edged past Tulsa 69-64 on Wednesday night. Damian Dunn had 17 points for Temple (10-6, 3-2 American Athletic Conference). Jahlil White added 11 points and 10 rebounds. Zach Hicks had 11 points. Jeriah Horne had 15 points for the Golden Hurricane (6-8, 0-3). Rey Idowu added 14 points. LaDavius Draine had 12 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
